net.zerobandwidth.android.lib.nonsense

Class NonsenseShipOrPub

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.zerobandwidth.android.lib.nonsense.NonsenseShipOrPub
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NonsenseGenerator

    public class NonsenseShipOrPub
extends java.lang.Object
implements NonsenseGenerator
    Builds a random name of a ship… or a pub… or something.

    Both ships and pubs seem to have names that follow the general pattern of "The <adjective> <noun>", like "The Salty Dog" or "The Mourning Glory" or "The Rapacious Tardigrade". OK, maybe not the last one. Anyway, since NonsenseBuilder worked out so well, and this is actually a simpler algorithm, it seemed only right to go ahead with this now.

    As with NonsenseBuilder, this class makes use of two of the array resources that are included with the library:

    • R.array#asNonsenseAdjectives
    • R.array#asNonsenseNouns

    Applications using this class may choose to have overrides for either or both of these string resources, in order to customize the text that might be rendered in the randomized names.

    Since:
    zerobandwidth-net/android 0.1.5 (#11)
